scintillating
	adj. sparkling or shining brightly
veracious
	adj. speaking or representing the truth
efflorescence
	n. the state or a period of flowering
precocious
	adj. (of a child) having developed certain abilities or proclivities at an earlier age than usual
impecunious
	adj. having little or no money
assiduous
	adj. showing great care and perseverance
hortatory
	adj. tending or aiming to exhort
exhort
	v. strongly encourage or urge (someone) to do something
ingenuous
	adj. innocent and unsuspecting
prevaricate
	v. avoid telling the truth by not directly answering the question